   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"# Executive Brief Generator\\n\",\"**NLP Project 90 of 100** — Condense long reports into executive-level summaries with key metrics and recommendations.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import re, requests\\nimport warnings; warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\\nprint('Loaded.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"REPORT = \\\"\\\"\\\"Q1 2025 Performance Report - Marketing Department\\n\\nRevenue increased by 15% to $2.4M compared to Q4 2024. Customer acquisition cost (CAC) decreased from $45 to $38. Email campaign open rates improved to 28% from 22%. Social media engagement grew 40% across all platforms. Website traffic reached 1.2M monthly visits, a new record.\\n\\nChallenges: Ad spend increased 20% without proportional ROI. Two major campaigns underperformed expectations. Team bandwidth constraints delayed the product launch campaign.\\n\\nRecommendations: 1) Reallocate 30% of ad budget from display to content marketing. 2) Hire two additional content creators. 3) Implement A/B testing framework for all campaigns. 4) Invest in marketing automation to improve team efficiency.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\ndef generate_brief(report):\\n    # Extract numbers/metrics\\n    metrics = re.findall(r'[\\\\d.]+%|\\\\$[\\\\d,.]+[MKB]?', report)\\n    # Extract recommendations\\n    recs = re.findall(r'\\\\d\\\\)\\\\s*([^.]+\\\\.)', report)\\n    # Key sentences (containing 'increased', 'decreased', 'improved', 'grew')\\n    sentences = re.split(r'(?<=[.!?])\\\\s+', report)\\n    highlights = [s for s in sentences if any(w in s.lower() for w in ['increased','decreased','improved','grew','record'])]\\n    \\n    brief = '📋 EXECUTIVE BRIEF\\\\n' + '='*40 + '\\\\n\\\\n'\\n    brief += '📊 Key Metrics:\\\\n'\\n    for m in metrics[:5]: brief += f'  • {m}\\\\n'\\n    brief += '\\\\n🔝 Highlights:\\\\n'\\n    for h in highlights[:3]: brief += f'  • {h.strip()}\\\\n'\\n    brief += '\\\\n💡 Recommendations:\\\\n'\\n    for r in recs[:3]: brief += f'  • {r.strip()}\\\\n'\\n    return brief\\n\\nprint(generate_brief(REPORT))\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"# LLM-based brief\\ndef llm_brief(report, model='qwen3:1.7b'):\\n    prompt = f'Generate a 5-sentence executive brief from this report. Focus on: 1) headline result, 2) key metrics, 3) main challenge, 4) top recommendation.\\\\n\\\\n{report} /no_think'\\n    try:\\n        r = requests.post('http://localhost:11434/api/generate',json={'model':model,'prompt':prompt,'stream':False},timeout=60)\\n        return r.json().get('response','')\\n    except: return 'Ollama unavailable.'\\n\\nprint('\\\\nLLM Brief:')\\nprint(llm_brief(REPORT))\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Summary\\n\",\"- **Executive briefs extract metrics, highlights, and recommendations.**\\n\",\"- **Rule-based extraction catches quantitative signals reliably.**\\n\",\"- **LLMs synthesize narrative summaries** with better flow.\\n\",\"- **For production, template the output format** for consistency across departments.\"]}\n",
    " ],\n",
